@startuml
title Viaverse Analytics Event / Alert — State Diagram

[*] --> CAPTURED
CAPTURED --> CONSENT_CHECKED : check
CONSENT_CHECKED --> SANITIZED : allowed
CONSENT_CHECKED --> RETENTION_EXPIRED : not allowed/drop
SANITIZED --> SCHEMA_VALIDATED : validate
SCHEMA_VALIDATED --> STORED : valid
SCHEMA_VALIDATED --> DLQ_SCHEMA_FAILED : invalid
STORED --> AGGREGATED : aggregate
AGGREGATED --> RETENTION_EXPIRED : retention policy
DLQ_SCHEMA_FAILED --> ALERT_RAISED : quality alert
AGGREGATED --> ALERT_RAISED : SLO/anomaly
ALERT_RAISED --> ALERT_RESOLVED : ack/resolved

RETENTION_EXPIRED --> [*]
ALERT_RESOLVED --> [*]

note bottom
Dropped or consent-blocked events should not be recoverable as user-level analytics.
Aggregates may remain only if privacy policy allows.
end note
@enduml
